answers.answer: I have the same due date.  I am also 1 cm dilated and 50% effaced. I have been having contractions for weeks now but I also feel over a baby gate a few weeks ago. I feel that these November babies are holding on for as long as possible.  I am hoping sometime this coming week I will give birth.  I would focus on how you're going to breathe through your contractions.... who knows maybe it will get you going!

Due the same too but being induced 11/17 and so ready. I'm swollen, tired, huge, acid reflux, back spasms, RLS bad, and my whole left side is swollen. Oh, and still don't have any sign of milk! Nervous but ready, and this is going to be the longest 6 days. Hopefully, he will come before; naturally!!!:-)

I'm due on the 22nd. Only 1cm dilated and just realized today I'm loosing my mucus plug. Already scheduled for induction which will be in the exact 41 wrk if she doesn't arrive. Also, I have intermittent contractions for several weeks now too.
Just found out i have high blood pressure. Waiting to be seen. This has never been a problem before. I wonder will they keep me in?
41 weeks oh my, and already showing signs of contractions. Good luck.High blood pressure they will keep you because it's a sign of preeclampsia. Good luck to you all!!! Keep us updated!!!
I am due on the 23rd and don't know how much my son weighs right now and have no idea how dilated I am. But I have been having strong contractions,  but they aren't regular.

After all the fussing i dont even have high blood pressure. It just went up because i was anxious after been waiting to be seen for so long. But i was told today i will be induced on my due date because baby is so big and loads of fluid. Fingers crossed everything will be ok untik then.

title: 23rd Nov
